"Brunklaus B., Thormark C., Baumann H.","Illustrating limitations of energy studies of buildings with LCA and actor analysis",2010,"Building Research and Information","38","3",,"265","279",,,10.1080/09613211003654871,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-77951525010&partnerID=40&md5=f0069c2071f30d1ec47db2668deccf59","Environmental Systems Analysis, Chalmers University of Technology, S-41296-Gothenburg, Sweden; Culture and Society,Urban Studies, MalmöUniversity, S-20506 Malmö, Sweden","Brunklaus, B., Environmental Systems Analysis, Chalmers University of Technology, S-41296-Gothenburg, Sweden; Thormark, C., Culture and Society,Urban Studies, MalmöUniversity, S-20506 Malmö, Sweden; Baumann, H., Environmental Systems Analysis, Chalmers University of Technology, S-41296-Gothenburg, Sweden","Does passive housing really have better environmental performance than conventional housing? Three passive houses and four conventional houses were compared using a life cycle assessment (LCA) methodology. The comparison also provided an actor analysis for the building supply chain and building inhabitants. Results are presented for two scenarios: 'conventional choices' and 'green choices' by the actors. The comparison confirms that passive houses have lower energy use than conventional houses, but when the environmental impact of energy production is taken into consideration, the outcome is less clear. Conventional houses can be equally good environmentally in terms of global warming, acidification, or radioactive waste as typical passive houses with electrical heating depending on the actors' choices. Actor analysis shows that inhabitants' and material producers' electricity choice are very important, while other choices (e.g. green transport) are less important. The findings highlight the importance of environmentally responsible decisions throughout the whole life cycle and the need for appropriate behaviours and actions, along with implications for improved communication. © 2010 Taylor & Francis.","Actor analysis; Environmental assessment; Housing; Inhabitant behaviour; Life cycle analysis (LCA); Low-carbon building; Passive house","Actor analysis; Environmental assessment; Inhabitant behaviour; Life cycle analysis; Life cycle analysis (LCA); Passive house; Buildings; Environmental impact; Global warming; Heating; Houses; Industrial waste treatment; Radioactive wastes; Supply chains; Life cycle",,,,,,"Adalberth, K., Almgren, A., Petersen, E.H., Life cycle assessment of four multi-family buildings. International (2001) Journal of Low Energy and Sustainable Buildings, 2, pp. 1-21; (2000) Livscyklusvurdering af Dansk el og Kraftvarme, , Anon, EnergiE2, Elkraft, Elsam, Elfor, Eltra; Axelsson, U., Jarnhammar, A., Widell, K.O., Jernberg, P., Jansson, G., Zackriasson, M., Holmer, O., (1999) Livscykelanalys Av Färg (vattenbaserad), , Report No. B1338-B, Swedish Environmental Institute IVL, Stockholm; Bagge, H., Elmroth, A., Lindstrii, L., (2004) Energianvändning och Inneklimat i Två Energieffektiva Småhus i Västra HamneniMalmö, , TVBH 04/3048SE 109, Building Physics, Lund Institute of Technology, Lund; Baumann, H., Environmental assessment of organizing - towards a framework for the study of organizational influence on environmental performance (2004) Progress in Industrial Ecology, 1 (1-3), pp. 292-306; Baumann, H., Tillman, A.M., (2004) The Hitch Hiker's Guide to LCA - an Orientation in Life Cycle Assessment Methodology and Application, , Studentliteratur, Lund; Baumann, H., Brunklaus, B., Gluch, P., Kadefors, A., Stenberg, A.C., Thuvander, L., (2003) Environmental Barometer for the Building Sector, , Miljöbarometern för byggsektorn 2002, Environmental Systems Analysis and Centrum för management i byggsektorn, ESA Report No. 2003:2, Chalmers University of Technology, Gothenburg; Beiron, J., Frodeson, S., Wikström, F., (2007) Lågenergihus Med. 44 Lägenheter. Drifterfarenheter, Driftstatistik Samt Miljöbedömning av energianvändning, 